Football is a game which most people in Dalbeattie are enthusiastic about. The senior team in the town is{ {Dalbeattie Star.}They once played Glasgow Celtic in the{Scottish Cup.}At the start of the Second World War Dalbeattie Star folded and reformed in the 70's.This year (1985),they won the {Southern Counties League.}
There is also a Sunday League in which two teams from Dalbeattie play.They are all pub teams in this League and the names of the two Dalbeattie teams are the{Crown}and the{Ship.
There are four different age groups, ranging from under tens to under sixteens, in a{Youth League}which was started two years ago by the parents of keen, young footballers.
